# Day 4 — Search & Text Processing

## 📌 Overview
On Day 4, I practised searching, filtering, counting, sorting, and editing text using essential Linux commands. These skills are important for log analysis and cloud security tasks.

## 🛠 Commands Practiced

### 🔍 grep — Search Text
- Search for specific words inside files
```bash
grep "error" test.txt
grep -i "failed" /var/log/auth.log
🔢 wc — Count Lines/Words
Count number of lines in a file
wc -l test.txt
🔗 Pipe (|)
Combine commands
grep "error" test.txt | wc -l
🔃 sort — Sort Data
Sort lines alphabetically
sort test.txt
🔁 uniq — Remove Duplicates
Remove duplicate lines
uniq test.txt
Count occurrences
sort test.txt | uniq -c
✏️ sed — Edit Text
Replace text in file
sed -i 's/error/WARNING/g' test.txt
📂 Files Used
test.txt

Sample log file containing:

error
login success
warning
login failed
🔍 Log Analysis Practice
grep -a "error" /var/log/syslog
grep -i "failed" /var/log/auth.log

👉 Learned how real system logs contain warnings, errors, and failures.
